      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of Sept 27 article on viewers' responses to Hip-Hop Nation exhibition at Brooklyn Museum of Art, regarding materials used by artist Chris Ofili for his collage in museum's recent show Sensation</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article yesterday about viewers' responses to the ''Hip-Hop Nation'' exhibition at the Brooklyn Museum of Art referred incorrectly to materials used by the artist Chris Ofili for his collage of the Virgin Mary in the museum's recent show ''Sensation.'' Along with paper, oil paint, glitter and resin, the artist used elephant dung, not cow dung.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
